The /metro-map page now uses the MBTiles file from assets/maps as a real offline Tehran basemap.

Current map data:
- Source file: assets/maps/osm-2020-02-10-v3.11_iran_tehran.mbtiles
- Format: OpenMapTiles vector MBTiles, PBF tiles, TMS scheme
- Extracted runtime tiles: public/maps/tehran/{z}/{x}/{y}.pbf
- Renderer: MapLibre GL

Why extraction is needed:
- Browsers cannot read SQLite MBTiles files directly.
- The script scripts/extract-mbtiles.mjs converts the MBTiles tile rows into normal web tile paths.
- The script also converts the MBTiles TMS row numbering into XYZ row numbering and decompresses gzip-wrapped PBF tiles.

How to regenerate local tiles:
- Put a compatible .mbtiles file in assets/maps.
- Run: node scripts/extract-mbtiles.mjs
- The generated public/maps/tehran folder is ignored by git because it is derived from the MBTiles file.

Runtime behavior:
- The app does not download map tiles from the internet.
- The map page overlays metro lines and stations from src/data/stations.json.
- Close station nodes are clustered and become selectable as you zoom in.
- The JPG metro diagram remains below the street map as a reference.
